Business Brief -- Syntex Corp.:
   Capital Outlays to Rise 27%
   During Current Fiscal Year
Paul E. Freiman, chairman and chief executive officer,
told a meeting of securities analysts that he expects
"business will be good this year," with the second half of
fiscal 1992 stronger than the first half.
   However, Mr. Freiman declined to comment on published
analysts' estimates that fiscal 1992 profit will fall to
$2.10 to $2.35 a share. For the year ended July 31, Syntex
reported profit of $423.8 million, or $1.89 a share, on
revenue of $1.82 billion.